description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a qualified and registered band 5 play specialist who is committed to the delivery of compassionate high quality care to join our established play team at the Whittington hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be to support patients across the units including Roses day care unit, Clinic 4D, Children&#39;s Ambulatory Unit, Ifor Ward, ED and some adult areas where CYP are seen. You will be working closely within the wider MDT to implement specialised play input to support the CYP and their families throughout their time in hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is important the applicants have good knowledge of distraction techniques and therapeutic play. Have the ability to plan, co-ordinate and apply therapeutic interventions for children and young people experiencing difficulties with medical interventions and their treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
